defaultFreedom from Torture default&#xa0;
defaultFreedom from Torture, formerly known as the Medical Foundation for the Care of Victims of Torture, is a UK-ba
defaultsed human rights organisation and one of the world’s largest torture treatment centres.  
defaultSince our foundation more than 25 years ago, more than 50,000 people 
defaulthave been referred to us 
defaultand we currently have centres in London, Manchester, Newcastle, Birmingham and Glasgow.  
default&#xa0;
defaultThe organisation exists to enable survivors of torture and organised violence to engage in a healing process to assert their own human dignity and worth.  
defaultOur concer
defaultn for the health and wellbeing of torture survivors and their families is directed towards providing 
defaultmedical, psychiatric and psychological consultation, assessment and treatment, short and long term rehabilitation through social care, casework and counsel
defaultling, psychotherapy, physiotherapy, complementary therapies, group and family work, as well as practical assistance with accommodation and welfare agencies.  Our holistic approach recognises the wellbeing of the whole person and that absence of access to j
defaultustice to secure protection and welfare and housing impacts adversely on torture survivors and can inhibit the efficacy of therapy.
default&#xa0;
defaultFreedom from Torture also accepts instructions for the preparation of forensic medico-legal reports documenting torture in 
defaultaccordance with the international standard set out in the Istanbul Protocol and the organisation prepares 
defaultbetween 
default300-600 medico-legal reports per year.  It is also our mission to educate decision-makers and the public about torture and its consequences, w
defaulthile our advocacy work strives to ensure that the UK and other states honour their international obligations with regard to torture.
