defaultAccess to justice is an important element of the right to rehabilitation, guaranteed to torture survivors by Article 14 of the UN Convention Aga
defaultinst Torture. In its recent General Comment on this article of the 
defaulttreaty
default, the Committee Against Torture emphasised that ‘
defaultthe provision of means for as full rehabilitation as possible for anyone who has suffered harm as a result of a violation of the Conve
defaultntion should be holistic and include medical and psychological care as well as 
defaultlegal
default and social services
default’
default (emphasis added).
default The Committee also affirmed that
default States parties to this treaty must ensure that access to justice is available to all torture victims including ‘asylum-seekers, refugees or others under international protection’. The UK has been a party to this treaty since 8 December 1988.  
